# Windows Service Status Monitoring in SigNoz

## Purpose

This document outlines the requirements, implementation options, testing results, and recommendation for monitoring Windows Service status (Running/Stopped) in SigNoz.

The objective is to provide visibility into the operational state of Windows Services running on Windows Servers and enable alerting when critical services stop unexpectedly.

---

# Executive Summary

SigNoz does not natively discover or monitor Windows Services running on Windows servers.

To collect Windows Service status metrics and send them to SigNoz, one of the following solutions must be deployed on the target Windows server:

1. Prometheus Windows Exporter (Recommended)
2. OpenTelemetry Collector with Windows Service Monitoring Components

Without one of these agents installed on the Windows host, SigNoz cannot determine:

* Which Windows Services exist
* Whether a service is Running or Stopped
* Service start mode information
* Service availability changes over time

Therefore, installation of either Windows Exporter or OpenTelemetry Collector is a mandatory prerequisite for Windows Service monitoring.

