# Solution Options

## Option 1: Prometheus Windows Exporter (Recommended)

### Overview

Windows Exporter is a Microsoft Windows monitoring agent that exposes operating system metrics in Prometheus format.

The exporter provides built-in service monitoring capabilities through the Service Collector.

### Architecture

```text
Windows Server
    │
    │ Windows Exporter
    │ Port 9182
    ▼
OpenTelemetry Collector
    │
    │ OTLP
    ▼
SigNoz OTel Collector
    ▼
ClickHouse
    ▼
SigNoz Dashboard
```

### Advantages

* Mature and widely adopted solution
* Simple deployment
* Native Windows Service metrics
* Supports additional metrics:

  * CPU
  * Memory
  * Disk
  * Network
  * Processes
* Minimal configuration required
* Industry-standard approach

### Metrics Available

Examples:

```text
windows_service_state
windows_service_status
windows_service_start_mode
```

### Example Service Metric

```text
windows_service_state{
    name="Spooler",
    state="running"
} 1
```

```text
windows_service_state{
    name="Spooler",
    state="stopped"
} 0
```

### Validation Performed

Testing was successfully completed on a local Windows environment.

Validation included:

* Installation of Windows Exporter
* Configuration of SigNoz OTel Collector Prometheus Receiver
* Metric ingestion into SigNoz
* Verification of:

  * Running services
  * Stopped services
  * Service counts
  * Service state transitions

