# Option 2: OpenTelemetry Collector Windows Service Monitoring

## Overview

OpenTelemetry Collector can collect Windows Service information directly through Windows-specific receivers and host monitoring components.

### Architecture

```text
Windows Server
    │
    │ OTel Collector
    ▼
SigNoz OTel Collector
    ▼
ClickHouse
    ▼
SigNoz Dashboard
```

### Advantages

* Native OpenTelemetry implementation
* No Prometheus exporter dependency
* Single observability agent

### Limitations

* Requires installation and maintenance of OpenTelemetry Collector on every Windows server
* More complex configuration
* Additional operational overhead
* Less commonly deployed for Windows service monitoring compared to Windows Exporter

### Deployment Requirements

For each Windows Server:

* Install OpenTelemetry Collector
* Configure Windows Service monitoring receiver
* Configure OTLP exporter
* Register as Windows Service
* Maintain configuration and upgrades

### Validation Status

A proof-of-concept configuration has been identified and tested.

However, implementation requires deployment and maintenance of the OpenTelemetry Collector service on each monitored Windows server.

Screenshots and configuration examples are available.

